<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3273: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-06T10:00:00-05:00">March 6, 1929—10
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>21. Your 27, March 3, noon. I very much hope that the Government of Chile
                            will not permit the question of the erection of the monument on the
                            Morro or the expense of the port to stand in the way of a definitive
                            settlement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>